oser to $q_{\\rm min}$ we find that extremely\nlow temperatures are required to observe the asymptotic behavior, due to the\ninfluence of the tricritical point at $q_{\\rm min}$, which leads to a\ncross-over at a temperature $T^*(q)$ between logarithmic tricritical scaling\nand zero-scale-factor universality, with $T^*(q)\\to 0$ when $q\\to q_{\\rm min}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Mar 2016 17:48:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 Feb 2017 16:51:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 26 May 2017 21:59:41 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-30"}
