{"id":"1603.04599","submitter":"Corina Ciobotaru","authors":"Corina Ciobotaru","title":"Infinitely generated Hecke algebras with infinite presentation","comments":"21 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RT math.GR math.RA","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For a locally compact group G and a compact subgroup K, the corresponding\nHecke algebra consists of all continuous compactly supported complex functions\non G that are K-bi-invariant. There are many examples of totally disconnected\nlocally compact groups whose Hecke algebras with respect to the maximal compact\nsubgroups are not commutative. One of those is the universal group U(F)^+, when\nF is primitive but not 2-transitive. For this class of groups we prove that the\nHecke algebra with respect to the maximal compact subgroup K is infinitely\ngenerated and infinitely presented. This may be relevant for constructing\nirreducible unitary representations of U(F)^+ whose subspace of K-fixed vectors\nhas dimension at least two, or answering the question whether U(F)^+ is a type\nI group or not. On the contrary, when F is 2-transitive that Hecke algebra of\nU(F)^+ is commutative, finitely generated admitting only one generator.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Mar 2016 09:11:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-03-16"}
